### User documentation ###

## Project overview ##
The Dell PowerFlex Manager 4.8. releae consisted of a new feature that automated the bootstrapper of PowerFlex nodes. From a content perspective, I had to design and write end user instructions on how to deploy PowerFlex nodes.

## Audience ##
The target audience for the content includes Dell Technologies customers and services.

## Objective ##
The objective of the content was to enable users to work through the steps a new initial welcome wizard that deployed PowerFlex nodes.

## Your role ##
My role was lead writer on the project.

## Deliverable ##
The deliverables were documnetation:
* Getting started with a PowerFlex deployment: https://www.dell.com/support/manuals/en-us/scaleio/powerflex_manager_user_guide_48x/getting-started-with-a-powerflex-deployment?guid=guid-ce499418-5c52-43c5-bfa0-2f6699a1099b&lang=en-us
* Planning and preparing: https://www.dell.com/support/manuals/en-us/scaleio/powerflex_manager_user_guide_48x/plan-and-prepare?guid=guid-7b7f637f-dd9d-4ccf-8da5-57c915c6acd9&lang=en-us
* Configuring the initial setup [https://www.dell.com/support/manuals/en-us/scaleio/powerflex_manager_user_guide_48x/configure-the-initial-setup?guid=guid-6c1973c2-cdb3-44df-9d2a-ca3ce1cc03db&lang=en-us
* Configuring PowerFlex nodes through the initail Welcome wizard [https://www.dell.com/support/manuals/en-us/scaleio/powerflex_manager_user_guide_48x/configure-powerflex-nodes-through-the-initial-welcome-wizard?guid=guid-0a8b8b58-d02f-4975-8639-e8f593de6c61&lang=en-us
